MANSION COMPOSE
====================

Compose files used to build the PTS "Mansion" server, designed to be as repro-
ducible as possible.

Rootless environment is recommended. Create one with root:
	useradd -m podmanager
	loginctl enable-linger podmanager

Web services share one virtual network:
	podman network create websrv


Applications
===============

acme.sh (acme-sh): Automatically renew TLS certificates
Manual steps:
	echo "CF_Token=<your_token>" > .env
	podman compose up -d
	podman exec acme.sh --set-default-ca --server letsencrypt
	podman exec acme.sh --issue -d <your_domain> --dns dns_cf
	podman exec acme.sh mkdir /cert/<your_domain>
	podman exec acme.sh --install-cert -d <your_domain> \
		--key-file /cert/<your_domain>/private.key \
		--fullchain-file /cert/<your_domain>/public.crt

NGINX (nginx): Reverse proxying
Manual steps:
	firewall-cmd --permanent --add-forward-port=port=80:proto=tcp:toport=9080
	firewall-cmd --permanent --add-forward-port=port=443:proto=tcp:toport=9443
	firewall-cmd --reload # 80 (Request) -> 9080 (Host) -> 80 (Container)
	podman compose up -d

MariaDB (mariadb): Database
- CURRENTLY DISABLED -
Manual steps:
	echo "<long_string>" | podman secret create mariadb_root_password -
	podman compose up -d

Memos (memos): One-man SNS
Manual steps:
	echo "postgres://memos:<long_string>@postgres:5432/memos?sslmode=disable" | podman secret create memos_connection -
	podman exec -it postgres psql -U postgres -W
	# Inside interactive SQL session
	create database memos;
	create user memos with password '<long_string>';
	grant all privileges on database memos to memos;
	alter database memos owner to memos;
	exit
	podman compose up -d

WordPress (wordpress): Blogging
- CURRENTLY DISABLED -
Manual steps:
	echo "<long_string>" | podman secret create wordpress_db_password
	podman exec -it mariadb bash
	# Inside container
	mariadb -u root -p"$(cat /run/secrets/mariadb_root_password)"
	# Inside interactive SQL session
	CREATE USER 'memos'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY '<long_string>';
	CREATE DATABASE memos;
	GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON memos.* TO 'memos'@'%';
	FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
	EXIT
	exit
	podman compose up -d

PostgreSQL (postgres): Database
Manual steps:
	echo "<long_string>" | podman secret create postgres_root_password
	podman compose up -d

Typecho (typecho): Blogging
- CURRENTLY DISABLED -
